{"questionId":"19304","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>In a class of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>30</mn></math> students, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>19</mn></math> play tennis, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> play both tennis and volleyball, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math> do not play&nbsp;either sport.</p>\n<p>The following Venn diagram shows the events “plays tennis” and “plays volleyball”.&nbsp;The values <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math> represent numbers of students.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/365586a2f181cba9bc60d4531c87c2665ed8901d.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>valid approach to find&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>eg&nbsp;</em>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>+</mo><mi>v</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>30</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>19</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>v</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp;(may be seen on Venn diagram)&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1 N2</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"19304","referenceCode":"20N.1.SL.TZ0.S_1a.ii","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of v.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a.ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.6—Combined, mutually exclusive, conditional, independence, prob diagrams"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}